# UI Component Conventions

## shadcn/ui

- Generated components live in `components/ui/` — **do not hand-edit** them.
- Add new shadcn components via `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`.
- Compose domain components from these primitives; never re-implement what shadcn already provides.

## Tailwind

- Use semantic CSS variables (defined in `app/globals.css`) instead of raw color values.
- Custom semantic tokens available in `tailwind.config.ts`:
  - `positive` / `negative` — gains/losses
  - `info` — neutral data callouts
  - Standard: `background`, `foreground`, `card`, `muted`, `border`, `ring`, `destructive`

```tsx
// ✅ semantic
<span className="text-positive">+4.2%</span>
<span className="text-negative">-1.8%</span>

// ❌ raw colour
<span className="text-green-500">+4.2%</span>
```

## Dark Mode

`next-themes` + Tailwind `darkMode: ["class"]` — always test both modes.
Use `dark:` variants for anything that isn't covered by CSS variables.

## Component Structure

```
components/
  ui/              # shadcn primitives (auto-generated)
  layout/          # Header, Sidenav — one responsibility each
  navigation/      # NavLinks, ProfileMenu, Sidenav
  [feature]/       # Domain components (watchlist, home, etc.)
```

- Client-only interactivity: add `"use client"` at the top of the file.
- Keep presentational components stateless; lift state to hooks.
- Icons: prefer `lucide-react`; `@heroicons/react` is also available.

## Responsive Design (Mobile-First)

Write mobile styles as the base, then layer up:

```tsx
// ✅ mobile-first
<div className="flex flex-col gap-2 md:flex-row md:gap-4 lg:gap-6">

// ❌ desktop-first with overrides
<div className="flex flex-row gap-6 max-md:flex-col max-md:gap-2">
```

Tailwind breakpoints: `sm` (640), `md` (768), `lg` (1024), `xl` (1280), `2xl` (1536).

## Images

Always use `next/image` with width/height:

```tsx
import Image from 'next/image';

<Image
  src="/chart.webp"
  alt="Sector performance chart"
  width={800}
  height={400}
  loading="lazy"
/>
```

- Prefer **WebP** (or AVIF) over PNG/JPG.
- Always provide `width` and `height` to avoid layout shift (CLS).
- Use `loading="lazy"` except for above-the-fold hero images (set `priority` instead).
- Remote images: whitelist the domain in `next.config.ts` `images.remotePatterns`.
